  <front>
    <title>Authentication and (D)TLS Profile for DNS-over-(D)TLS</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-ietf-dprive-dtls-and-tls-profiles-02"/>
    <author initials="S." surname="Dickinson" fullname="Sara Dickinson"/>
    <author initials="D. K." surname="Gillmor" fullname="Daniel Kahn Gillmor"/>
    <author initials="T." surname="Reddy.K" fullname="Tirumaleswar Reddy.K"/>
    <date day="10" month="June" year="2016"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>   This document describes how a DNS client can use a domain name to
   authenticate a DNS server that uses Transport Layer Security (TLS)
   and Datagram TLS (DTLS).  Additionally, it defines (D)TLS profiles
   for DNS clients and servers implementing DNS-over-TLS and DNS-over-
   DTLS.

	 </t>
